  <prompt>
    Take a FRESH authoritative snapshot of master branch protection state immediately before cutover. This is the rollback source-of-truth per spec §152 (rollback step 1: "Flip branch protection back to pre-cutover state saved to notes/branch-protection-pre-cutover.json"). Do NOT rely on the older `projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/baseline/branch-protection-2026-06-01.json` — take fresh snapshot now.
  </prompt>

  <role>CI/CD engineer capturing the rollback baseline immediately before flip.</role>

  <goal>`notes/branch-protection-pre-cutover.json` exists with current authoritative branch-protection state.</goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/ci-cd-unit-test-remediation-r1/spec.md (§152 rollback)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-A06">Pre-cutover state exported to `notes/branch-protection-pre-cutover.json`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec rollback">This file is the round-trip source for rollback — must be byte-exact restorable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project autonomous">FULL rigor — this gates the cutover.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify all Phase 2 dependencies are complete (053c merged; all workflow + skill changes merged)</step>
    <step order="2">`gh api repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection > projects/ci-cd-unit-test-remediation-r1/notes/branch-protection-pre-cutover.json`</step>
    <step order="3">Validate JSON is well-formed and contains expected fields (required_status_checks, restrictions, enforce_admins, etc.)</step>
    <step order="4">Commit + push (DO NOT modify branch protection in this task — that's task 071)</step>
    <step order="5">Document in notes: snapshot timestamp, repo state at snapshot, expected restore command for rollback</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="notes">projects/ci-cd-unit-test-remediation-r1/notes/branch-protection-pre-cutover.json</output>
    <output type="notes">projects/ci-cd-unit-test-remediation-r1/notes/branch-protection-snapshot-meta.md (timestamp, restore command)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">JSON file exists and is well-formed</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">JSON contains required_status_checks block</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Meta document explains how to round-trip restore</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All Phase 2 dependencies verified complete before snapshot</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
